  "original_title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s CEB price hike delayed, affecting CPC and monetary policy: CB Governor",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka\u2019s CEB price hike delayed, affecting CPC and monetary policy: CB Governor",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 A delay in hiking electricity prices has hit the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation cashflows despite the petroleum utility operating a price formula, Central Bank Governor Nandalal Weerasinghe said.",
        "Ceylon Petroleum Corporation has started operating a pricing formula but here is still a cashflow gap, he said.",
        "\u201cThey do not have enough rupees to buy dollars,\u201d Governor Weerasinghe said. \u201cCPC is still asking rupees from Treasury. So they are asking central bank to print money.\u201d",
        "The Ceylon Electricity Board was making losses, but there has been a delay in raising prices, he said.",
        "\u201cThough the CPC is selling oil it is not getting enough rupees from the CEB.\u201d",
        "CPC is asking 217 billion rupees from Treasury. So they ask from the Central Bank.",
        "\u201cWe are facing the consequences of not raising prices on time,\u201d he said. \u201cWe have to do these reforms.\u201d",
        "However the central bank alone cannot solve the problem and state enterprises and budgets, also have to be fixed, he said. (Colombo/July07/2022)"
      ],
